  "texts": [
    "All study data (GSES items, LLM responses, reasoning text) was recorded to a data table.",
    "Descriptive statistics include mean, standard deviation, median, interquartile range (IQR), and normality with the Shapiro-Wilk test.",
    "Answers to all tasks were graded on a binary rubric for correctness, and notes were taken describing different types of errors.",
    "Linear Mixed Effects 27 (LME) using Satterthwaite's (for each model) and Kenward-Roger's (for each task) approximation of the degrees of freedom tested for significant differences in self-assessment scores in each task.",
    "Post-hoc pairwise analysis was conducted with Estimated Marginal Means 28 using Tukey's (model A vs. model B in task C) approach to significance."
  ],
